article.headline: Arizona 66, Hawaii 57
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Dee-Dee Wheeler scored nine of her 18 points
during a key second-half run in No. 21 Arizona's 66-57 victory over
Hawaii in the fifth-place game of the Rainbow Wahine Classic.

Wheeler scored nine straight points in a 12-6 Arizona run that
broke a 41-41 tie in the second half and gave the Wildcats (3-2)
the lead for good.

Danielle Adefeso added 12 points, and Amy Gryzb had 11.

Hawaii got within two points three times midway through the
second half, the last on Jade Abele's jumper with 6:10 remaining.
But Arizona held the Rainbow Wahine scoreless for the next four
minutes and built the lead back up to eight.

Callie Spooner's two free throws broke the drought, the last
Hawaii would score in the game.

Abele led Hawaii (1-4) with 21 points, and Pam Tambini added 11.
